content.$t: answers: From the airport there are many options for getting into the city. There is a $5 shuttle to the Back Bay and even cheaper rides on the MBTA. There is taxi service and door to door shuttles. The MBTA is by far the best option as it is inexpensive and runs quite often- a shuttle that will take you to the Airport Blue line subway stop. There is also the SL1 which is a bus from the airport to the heart of downtown, South Station, the main train and bus hub for Boston. Lyft and Uber are also allowed to drop-off and pickup from the airport., otherlink: https://www.massport.com/logan-airport/to-and-from-logan/logan-express/back-bay/
